  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0b9a\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bbf \u0baa\u0bcb\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b95\u0bc7 \u0b89\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f 9 \u0baa\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0baa\u0bbf\u0ba3\u0bc8 - \u0b87\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bca\u0b9f\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "9 people, including lawyer Popake, who were arrested at the protest site, are on bail - two are still in hospital.",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "In relation to those who stayed at the protest site of Galli Mukhattidal Kota Ko Kama, today (22) morning, the Fort Court ordered the release of 9 people, including lawyer Nuvan Popake, who were arrested during the action taken by the security forces.",
        "While two of the 9 persons were injured in the attack by the security forces and are being treated in the hospital, the other 7 persons were produced in the Fort Magistrate's Court this evening in the presence of Deputy Magistrate Jayantha Dias Nanayakkara.",
        "Meanwhile, the judge allowed them to go on cash bail of Rs 10,000 each and two body bonds worth Rs 5 lakh each.",
        "The judge also stipulated that the suspects should not enter the presidential secretariat premises.",
        "Deputy Solicitor General Janaka Bandara appeared on behalf of the Attorney General along with Senior Superintendent of Police Roshan Dias, Assistant Superintendent of Police Villava Arachi, and Officer-in-Charge of Fort Sagara Lienake on behalf of the complainant.",
        "Deputy Solicitor General Janaka Bandara stated that the suspects are being charged with being a member of an illegal assembly and obstructing the duties of public servants, applying pressure and causing damage to the Presidential Secretariat, which is a public property.",
        "However, for the suspects, 320 lawyers, including President's lawyers Riensi Arsakularatne, Sarath Jayamanna, Upul Jayasuriya, Saliya Peiris, senior lawyers Darshana Kruuppu, Gunaratna Vanninayake appeared.",
        "They argued that the case was tested and that the suspects had no connection with the allegations and demanded an investigation into the assault on the suspects.",
        "They noted that those who ordered the attack had instead arrested the perpetrators and placed the victims as suspects.",
        "Judge Jayantha Dias Nanayakkara, who investigated the matter, released all the suspects on bail and adjourned the case to the 26th."
      ],
